cook...i think that if i see that my country is wrong, and making mistakes, it's my duty to improve it, change it if i can, and if i can't, i may chose to not take part. which is what i did, simple as that...<br><br>
18 year olds got the right to vote in 1971, i was about to be drafted in 68, before i could vote..it's slavery when a man puts a gun in your ribs and takes you from your family and by another name, they call it the draft. there was no honor in our being in RVN, our freedoms were never threatened, nor were the french freedoms at risk.<br><br>
when help is needed to secure the home front, i'll be there,  or to help a friend in need. VN was not that call.<br><br>
